16/09/2004
BRCKO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- SFOR handed over a former base, Camp McGovern, to Brcko District civil authorities Wednesday (15 September).
During the ceremony, officials said the event represented a high mark in the country's stabilisation process.
High Representative Paddy Ashdown called on Brcko's politicians and citizens to take advantage of the progress achieved in the nine years since the war ended.
In other news, Republika Srpska Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic said Wednesday that BiH's military attach√© to NATO headquarters in Brussels, Darko Matijasevic, is the most likely candidate for the post of interior minister.
Matijasevic successfully passed the Office of the High Representative's vetting process.
Also Wednesday, members of the tripartite BiH presidency met with Timothy Cartwright, the head of a CoE monitoring mission in Sarajevo.
He urged the full implementation of recently passed legislation.
(OHR Sources, Fena, PBS BiH - 16/09/04;
Pincom.info, Nina - 15/09/04)
